<< /Length 739 >>
stream
BT
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (4. EXISTING SYSTEM AND PROPOSED SYSTEM) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 706 Td (Existing System: Farmers usually receive agricultural information through long) Tj
72 691 Td (advisories, PDF documents, WhatsApp messages, or verbal communication. These methods) Tj
72 676 Td (may not be interactive, searchable, or personalized. Expert consultation may also take) Tj
72 661 Td (time and may not be digitally tracked.) Tj
72 638 Td (Proposed System: Raitha-Varta provides a mobile-first advisory system. Farmers can) Tj
72 623 Td (view short tips, filter by crop, submit leaf problems, and receive bilingual outcomes.) Tj
72 608 Td (The backend stores data and provides an Expert Dashboard for advisory management.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
24 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 25 0 R >>
endobj
25 0 obj
<< /Length 677 >>
stream
BT
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (5. SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 706 Td (Hardware Requirements: Android phone or emulator, minimum 4 GB RAM development system,) Tj
72 691 Td (internet or local network connection for backend testing.) Tj
72 668 Td (Software Requirements: Android Studio, Kotlin, Gradle, Node.js runtime, Android SDK,) Tj
72 653 Td (browser for Expert Dashboard.) Tj
72 630 Td (Android Libraries: ViewPager2, Room Database, Retrofit, Gson Converter, Glide,) Tj
72 615 Td (AppCompat, Material Components.) Tj
72 592 Td (Backend Technologies: Node.js HTTP server, REST API, JSON file storage, HTML, CSS, and) Tj
72 577 Td (JavaScript dashboard.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
26 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 27 0 R >>
endobj
27 0 obj
<< /Length 794 >>
stream
BT
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (6. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 706 Td (The architecture consists of three major layers: Android Farmer App, Backend API) Tj
72 691 Td (Server, and Expert Dashboard.) Tj
72 668 Td (Android Farmer App: Provides UI, flash cards, crop filters, Room offline database,) Tj
72 653 Td (Retrofit API calls, and leaf-photo selection.) Tj
72 630 Td (Backend API Server: Provides endpoints for tips, expert requests, and expert replies.) Tj
72 615 Td (It stores requests in a JSON file for persistence.) Tj
72 592 Td (Expert Dashboard: Provides a browser interface for experts to view requests and update) Tj
72 577 Td (Kannada and English outcomes.) Tj
72 554 Td (Flow: Farmer App -> Backend API -> Expert Dashboard -> Expert Reply -> Stored Outcome.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
28 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 29 0 R >>
endobj
29 0 obj
<< /Length 965 >>
stream
BT
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (7. MODULES DESCRIPTION) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 706 Td (Daily Tips Module: Shows crop advisory cards with image, crop category, district,) Tj
72 691 Td (weather note, success story, Kannada tip, and English instruction.) Tj
72 668 Td (Crop Filter Module: Allows farmers to filter tips based on crop categories including) Tj
72 653 Td (Paddy, Arecanut, Coconut, and Tomato.) Tj
72 630 Td (Offline Storage Module: Uses Room Database to save tips locally so that farmers can) Tj
72 615 Td (view advisory cards even when offline.) Tj
72 592 Td (Expert Ask Module: Allows farmers to enter name, crop, district, problem, and choose a) Tj
72 577 Td (leaf photo from the device.) Tj
72 554 Td (Backend API Module: Handles REST endpoints for tips, expert requests, and expert) Tj
72 539 Td (replies.) Tj
72 516 Td (Expert Dashboard Module: Enables experts to view farmer requests and save Kannada and) Tj
72 501 Td (English outcomes.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
30 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 31 0 R >>
endobj
31 0 obj
<< /Length 1036 >>
stream
BT
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (8. IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 706 Td (The Android app is implemented in Kotlin using XML layouts. ViewPager2 is used for the) Tj
72 691 Td (flash-card experience. The TipAdapter binds each farming tip to the card view. Glide) Tj
72 676 Td (is used for crop images. Room Database is used to store advisory data for offline) Tj
72 661 Td (access.) Tj
72 638 Td (Retrofit is used to communicate with the backend. The RetrofitClient connects to the) Tj
72 623 Td (backend API using the local system IP address. The Expert Ask form uses Android photo) Tj
72 608 Td (picker support to select a leaf image and sends the selected URI to the backend.) Tj
72 585 Td (The backend is implemented using Node.js without external npm dependencies. It exposes) Tj
72 570 Td (REST endpoints and stores Expert Ask data in expert-asks.json. The dashboard page is) Tj
72 555 Td (served from the backend itself and uses JavaScript fetch calls to display and update) Tj
72 540 Td (expert outcomes.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
32 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R >> >> /Contents 33 0 R >>
endobj
33 0 obj
<< /Length 619 >>
stream
BT
/F1 18 Tf
72 742 Td (9. TESTING) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
72 706 Td (Unit and functional testing were performed manually for the main features. The app was) Tj
72 691 Td (tested for loading tips, filtering crop categories, offline Room data display, backend) Tj
72 676 Td (tip fetching, leaf photo selection, and expert request submission.) Tj
72 653 Td (Backend testing included GET /api/tips, GET /api/expert-asks, POST /api/expert-asks,) Tj
72 638 Td (POST /api/expert-asks/:id/reply, and GET /dashboard. The dashboard was verified in the) Tj
72 623 Td (browser and confirmed to show saved farmer requests.) Tj
ET

endstream
endobj
